  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small pieces</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[275ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-8-1657642074503-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-8-1657642074503-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-8-1657642074503-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-8-1657642074503-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-8-1657642074503-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a<strong> </strong>generous<strong> </strong>drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add<strong> </strong>the<strong> chopped potatoes </strong>with the <strong>tomato stock</strong> and cook, covered, for an initial 10-12 min or until tender</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-8-1657642079435-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-8-1657642079435-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-8-1657642079435-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-8-1657642079435-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-8-1657642079435-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, deseed your <strong>peppers </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-7-1657642084314-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-7-1657642084314-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-7-1657642084314-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-7-1657642084314-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-7-1657642084314-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender, add your <strong>smoked paprika </strong>and<strong> half </strong>the<strong> grated garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>diced peppers</strong>, <strong>chopped onion</strong>,<strong> diced chorizo </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>cider vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>and cook for 4-5 min further or until starting to crisp – this is your <strong>smoky</strong> <strong>chorizo hash</strong></p><p>Tip: Stir the pan occasionally to prevent everything from sticking!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-8-1657642089202-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-8-1657642089202-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-8-1657642089202-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-8-1657642089202-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-8-1657642089202-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>parsley </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Combine your <strong>natural</strong> <strong>yoghurt</strong> and <strong>remaining grated garlic</strong> (don't like raw garlic? Just add a little!) in a small bowl with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) – this is your <strong>garlic yoghurt</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-8-1657642094344-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-8-1657642094344-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-8-1657642094344-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-8-1657642094344-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-8-1657642094344-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>cider vinegar</strong> to a bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>salad</strong> to the bowl and toss – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-8-1657642100569-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-8-1657642100569-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-8-1657642100569-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-8-1657642100569-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-8-1657642100569-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bring a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Crack your <strong>eggs</strong> gently into the water and leave them for 3 min</p><p>Once done, gently transfer the <strong>eggs</strong> with a slotted spoon to kitchen paper or a clean tea-towel and season them with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – these are your <strong>poached eggs</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-8-1657642105845-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-8-1657642105845-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-8-1657642105845-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-8-1657642105845-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-8-1657642105845-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, top the <strong>smoky</strong> <strong>chorizo hash </strong>with a<strong> poached egg </strong>and serve the <strong>dressed salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Dollop over the <strong>garlic yoghurt </strong>and sprinkle the<strong> remaining parsley </strong>all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
